title: Black Bean Chicken with Rice
directions: 1. In a small bowl, mix seasonings; sprinkle over both sides of chicken. In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Brown chicken on both sides.

2. Add beans, corn and salsa to skillet; cook, covered, 10-15 minutes or until a thermometer inserted in chicken reads 165Â°. Remove chicken from pan; cut into slices. Serve with bean mixture and rice.
ingredients: 4 boneless skinless chicken breast halves (4 ounces each)
1 can (15 ounces) black beans, rinsed and drained
